again another one two minutes about three

01:58:40.780 --> 01:58:43.180
four minutes in total it's like i told

01:58:43.180 --> 01:58:45.320
james i'm going to the u.s but what i

01:58:45.320 --> 01:58:47.240
have to say is this it was those four

01:58:47.240 --> 01:58:50.280
four minutes but four minutes that felt

01:58:50.280 --> 01:58:52.860
like an eternity i was still wondering

01:58:52.860 --> 01:58:56.940
this morning we who work in intensive care

01:58:56.940 --> 01:59:00.600
we examine a patient and we want to come

01:59:00.600 --> 01:59:02.240
back the next day to see how they're doing

01:59:02.240 --> 01:59:05.480
if they've improved if they haven't to this

01:59:05.480 --> 01:59:07.480
day i still want to go back there to see if

01:59:07.480 --> 01:59:11.520
he's left yet you know what i mean you get

01:59:11.520 --> 01:59:14.820
worried not all patients we don't get

01:59:14.820 --> 01:59:17.900
emotionally attached to everyone but we

01:59:17.900 --> 01:59:20.160
do with some with children with the

01:59:20.160 --> 01:59:23.200
