03:19:29.500 --> 03:19:37.500
Our professor here, who gave the testimony, Carlos, said it was tubular and didn't have lights, right?

03:19:37.500 --> 03:19:40.500
So, there are things that sometimes involve two spaceships, you know?

03:19:40.500 --> 03:19:44.500
So, the witnesses are that common, though.

03:19:44.500 --> 03:19:48.500
Like, James, how many witnesses do you think you've spoken to, total?

03:19:48.500 --> 03:19:56.500
Well, when I went downtown to the town square, I found a number of people that either saw…

03:19:56.500 --> 03:20:01.500
I mean, within an hour, I probably had 12 different people saying different things.

03:20:01.500 --> 03:20:03.500
One of them saw excessive…

03:20:03.500 --> 03:20:06.500
A couple of them saw excessive military activity they'd never seen before.

03:20:06.500 --> 03:20:08.500
Military trucks everywhere.

03:20:08.500 --> 03:20:12.500
If you were to add up everybody, though, and put an approximate number on it…

03:20:12.500 --> 03:20:14.500
Oh, God.

03:20:14.500 --> 03:20:18.500
And a witness, is anybody who's seen a ship or an alien body?

03:20:18.500 --> 03:20:20.500
Ship or alien body?

03:20:20.500 --> 03:20:25.500
Ship, maybe 12 to 15.

03:20:25.500 --> 03:20:29.500
I met another one recently who said he saw it over the hospital, maybe 15.

03:20:29.500 --> 03:20:31.500
And then the alien body, I think it's up to five.

03:20:31.500 --> 03:20:32.500
Wow.

03:20:32.500 --> 03:20:33.500
Yeah.

03:20:33.500 --> 03:20:34.500
It's pretty amazing.

03:20:34.500 --> 03:20:36.500
Yeah, and one of that includes the chief of police.

03:20:36.500 --> 03:20:39.500
I don't know any other case where you have that many witnesses.

03:20:39.500 --> 03:20:41.500
Then the three girls, Italo…

03:20:41.500 --> 03:20:43.500
Well, the nurse, that would have been six.

03:20:43.500 --> 03:20:45.500
So, it could be six that saw the…

03:20:45.500 --> 03:20:46.500
Yeah.

03:20:46.500 --> 03:20:52.500
Can you speak a little bit to Italo's credentials and kind of Bonafide's background?

03:20:52.500 --> 03:20:58.500
Because I think having a neurosurgeon come forward and say he was face to face with an

03:20:58.500 --> 03:21:05.500
alien being for three to four minutes is just going to be, A, so earth shattering for so

03:21:05.500 --> 03:21:08.500
many people, but B, I think very hard for them to compute.

03:21:08.500 --> 03:21:13.500
And I think they're going to often try to throw the kitchen sink of skepticism against this case.

03:21:13.500 --> 03:21:16.500
What's your experience of Italo?

03:21:16.500 --> 03:21:21.500
And what do you know about him and his reputation and his skills as a neurosurgeon?

03:21:21.500 --> 03:21:24.500
Dr. Italo is a very experienced doctor.

03:21:24.500 --> 03:21:27.500
Has a lot of credibility.

03:21:27.500 --> 03:21:30.500
Very honorable.

03:21:30.500 --> 03:21:42.500
Dr. To give this recent account of having personally seen and witnessed an extraterrestrial.

03:21:42.500 --> 03:21:47.500
And one of the reasons I'm here is because he's the one who gave the testimony.

03:21:47.500 --> 03:21:49.500
So, I trust in him.

03:21:49.500 --> 03:21:53.500
Now, of course, it's not common.

03:21:53.500 --> 03:22:01.500
Maybe if it were me on that day and I had seen the ET, I would have told my wife, my colleagues,

03:22:01.500 --> 03:22:04.500
would have called the hospital and said, look at this, how interesting.

03:22:04.500 --> 03:22:06.500
Each with their own reasons.

03:22:06.500 --> 03:22:10.500
Each with their own particularities and singularities.

03:22:10.500 --> 03:22:12.500
And I respect that.

03:22:12.500 --> 03:22:19.500
I don't depend on a private practice to make a living.

03:22:19.500 --> 03:22:22.500
He's a neurologist with a private practice.

03:22:22.500 --> 03:22:29.500
And this could really be a reason for losing clients in a private practice.

03:22:29.500 --> 03:22:33.500
With people thinking he was crazy, that he was seeing things.

03:22:33.500 --> 03:22:36.500
It could harm him professionally.

03:22:36.500 --> 03:22:39.500
And he justified his reasons.

03:22:39.500 --> 03:22:41.500
So that's plausible.

03:22:41.500 --> 03:22:42.500
It's understandable.

03:22:42.500 --> 03:22:44.500
But it's not common.

03:22:44.500 --> 03:22:50.500
I think perhaps most doctors or any citizen would have said, look, folks, there was a different

03:22:50.500 --> 03:22:53.500
situation today inside the hospital.

03:22:53.500 --> 03:22:55.500
But we have to respect it.

03:22:55.500 --> 03:23:04.500
And Marco Charisi's family to this day maintains that his injury was probably due to an alien

03:23:04.500 --> 03:23:10.500
being and that he was saying towards the end of his life constantly that he was worried

03:23:10.500 --> 03:23:14.500
that he was sick because he had apprehended this being and held him.

03:23:14.500 --> 03:23:19.500
And apparently the alien was full of kind of this greasy, oily substance.

03:23:19.500 --> 03:23:21.500
And that might have gotten on to him.

03:23:21.500 --> 03:23:27.500
And he was asking questions about what might occur if you come into contact with that because

03:23:27.500 --> 03:23:29.500
he was not feeling well.

03:23:29.500 --> 03:23:38.500
So his sister's testimony regarding the virulence of the bacteria, this leads us to believe that

03:23:38.500 --> 03:23:44.500
he may have participated in an operation to capture the CT.

03:23:44.500 --> 03:23:49.500
But that's not what I received through the colonel who requested the autopsy.

03:23:49.500 --> 03:23:51.500
He's a forensic doctor.

03:23:51.500 --> 03:23:54.500
But years later, that's what has been reaching us.

03:23:54.500 --> 03:23:59.500
And there are testimonies saying that from Marco Elicerenzi's sister.

03:23:59.500 --> 03:24:09.500
And also because of the evidence regarding the characteristics of the bacteria that was found in the soldier.

03:24:09.500 --> 03:24:14.500
What did the colonel say when he tasked you to do the autopsy?

03:24:14.500 --> 03:24:19.500
What did he share with you about the details?

03:24:19.500 --> 03:24:22.500
He didn't speak to me.

03:24:22.500 --> 03:24:28.500
The request was for a written coroner autopsy of the soldier.

03:24:28.500 --> 03:24:34.500
And it's not common for someone who normally requests an autopsy to be a police chief.

03:24:34.500 --> 03:24:40.500
It arrived, and they can also request it, just as the public prosecutor's office can request it for an autopsy.

03:24:40.500 --> 03:24:46.500
We performed the autopsy, awaited the lab tests, and about 20 days later we released the report,

03:24:46.500 --> 03:24:48.500
after the material from Lotto Giannini arrived.

03:24:48.500 --> 03:24:52.500
But I didn't speak with the commander of the military police.

03:24:52.500 --> 03:24:58.500
The autopsy was done to investigate an error, a supposed professional error, which was later not proven.

03:24:58.500 --> 03:24:59.500
Professional error.

03:24:59.500 --> 03:25:02.500
It was a progression of the medical complication.

03:25:02.500 --> 03:25:09.500
The doctor who performed this minor procedure, an excellent professional, has a very good reputation in the city.

03:25:09.500 --> 03:25:11.500
There were no complications.

03:25:11.500 --> 03:25:13.500
The progression of the disease was extremely unfavorable.

03:25:13.500 --> 03:25:16.500
Tell me about Dr. Giannini and his background.

03:25:16.500 --> 03:25:20.500
I think a lot of people found it very powerful in James' movie,

03:25:20.500 --> 03:25:27.500
when you have a guy who's kind of known as the godfather of medical science in the local region.

03:25:27.500 --> 03:25:29.500
And he's coming out and he's speculating.

03:25:29.500 --> 03:25:37.500
He literally says he thinks that a puncture wound from the nail of the ET is what caused Marco Scheresi's death.

03:25:37.500 --> 03:25:42.500
He sent it, and I've already left it with you, signed.

03:25:42.500 --> 03:25:46.500
He couldn't be here today because of health issues.

03:25:46.500 --> 03:25:48.500
He's almost 90 years old.

03:25:48.500 --> 03:25:50.500
But he's keeping up to speed with us.

03:25:50.500 --> 03:25:57.500
And made it a point to send us signed and authenticated document so it could be read, and I already left it to your care.

03:25:57.500 --> 03:25:59.500
But who is Dr. Giannini?

03:25:59.500 --> 03:26:07.500
He arrived in Varginha about 50 years ago, probably 45 or 50 years ago.

03:26:07.500 --> 03:26:10.500
He came from Rio de Janeiro and Brasília.

03:26:10.500 --> 03:26:18.500
He was a university professor, a pathologist and a forensic doctor in the state of Rio de Janeiro.

03:26:18.500 --> 03:26:25.500
He arrived in Varginha and set up a diagnostic and laboratory service, the Propedutic Institute,

03:26:25.500 --> 03:26:32.500
which serves practically 90% of its patients through the SUS, the Unified Health System.

03:26:32.500 --> 03:26:34.500
He serves the public health service.

03:26:34.500 --> 03:26:38.500
He's a reference for doctors working in the public health system.

03:26:38.500 --> 03:26:46.500
Today, he and his son, along with their entire staff, serve more than 100 cities in the region.

03:26:46.500 --> 03:26:48.500
So, he is a reference in quality.

03:26:48.500 --> 03:26:50.500
I'm not going to advertise, but it's true.

03:26:50.500 --> 03:26:53.500
He's a man unconcerned with monetary values.

03:26:53.500 --> 03:27:01.500
He values quality in his work as a scientist, seeking excellence in care and quality.

03:27:01.500 --> 03:27:06.500
And for us doctors, he always has been, and still is, a reference.

03:27:06.500 --> 03:27:08.500
Because he's a true scientist.

03:27:08.500 --> 03:27:16.500
And in this case, every time it was me, Dr. José da Frota, Dr. Ulisses Fernando, the forensic doctors there,

03:27:16.500 --> 03:27:20.500
when we had a more delicate case, when we had doubts, we would call him.

03:27:20.500 --> 03:27:25.500
And he'd be very willing, because Varginha is a small town, everything is nearby.

03:27:25.500 --> 03:27:28.500
I'll be there in 10 minutes, I'll assist with the autopsy.

03:27:28.500 --> 03:27:34.500
And he would assist, which sometimes meant performing the procedure, collecting materials.

03:27:34.500 --> 03:27:38.500
Said he'd take them to his laboratory, and giving the results in a week.

03:27:38.500 --> 03:27:43.500
And sometimes during the autopsy itself, during the examination, as a great pathologist,

03:27:43.500 --> 03:27:45.500
he would already give diagnoses.

03:27:45.500 --> 03:27:51.500
So, not only in forensic medicine, and in the area of autopsies, laboratories, biopsies.

03:27:51.500 --> 03:27:53.500
He's a huge reference.

03:27:53.500 --> 03:27:56.500
So, he has our respect, and we are very grateful to him.

03:27:56.500 --> 03:28:02.500
The doctors of Varginha have great respect and gratitude for Dr. João Batista Macucuzanini.

03:28:02.500 --> 03:28:13.500
Was there anything else about the body, outside of the bizarre bacteria, and Marco Charisi's stated story that he kept repeating with his family,

03:28:13.500 --> 03:28:16.500
that makes you think maybe there was some alien involvement?

03:28:16.500 --> 03:28:19.500
Was there a smell to it? Was there anything else about it?

03:28:19.500 --> 03:28:25.500
I hadn't met the soldier when he was alive.

03:28:25.500 --> 03:28:29.500
The first time I saw him, it was a body, ready to be autopsied.

03:28:29.500 --> 03:28:32.500
I never met him. I did meet some relatives.

03:28:32.500 --> 03:28:35.500
But not him. I had never seen him.

03:28:35.500 --> 03:28:40.500
But the sister's testimony, which is questionable.

03:28:40.500 --> 03:28:47.500
It's said that maybe he spoke to the doctors who tended to him at the hospital.

03:28:47.500 --> 03:28:52.500
But I don't have the testimony of those doctors that tended to him.

03:28:52.500 --> 03:28:56.500
But I heard his sister saying, which was recorded recently,

03:28:56.500 --> 03:29:01.500
that he was indeed involved in the capture of the ET.

03:29:01.500 --> 03:29:03.500
So, it's a puzzle.

03:29:03.500 --> 03:29:05.500
There are several moments we have there.

03:29:05.500 --> 03:29:15.500
People close to Varginha, who saw a ship the size of a bus heading towards the city in those days.

03:29:15.500 --> 03:29:20.500
For instance, take the testimony of the girls who saw the ET during the day.

03:29:20.500 --> 03:29:22.500
Today they are ladies.

03:29:22.500 --> 03:29:25.500
It's been 30 years. There were girls then. Today they are ladies.

03:29:25.500 --> 03:29:30.500
You see the testimony of Professor Carlos, a geography teacher,

03:29:30.500 --> 03:29:38.500
who gives a powerful account of having actually seen the spacecraft and its wreckage,

03:29:38.500 --> 03:29:39.500
and that he even touched it.

03:29:39.500 --> 03:29:43.500
But the police took it from him and ordered it handed over to the army.

03:29:43.500 --> 03:29:46.500
You also see the testimony of Dr. Italu.

03:29:46.500 --> 03:29:51.500
So, this makes us believe, in fact, in the existence of extraterrestrials on Earth.

03:29:51.500 --> 03:29:53.500
Not the Varginha ET.

03:29:53.500 --> 03:30:01.500
But this is a subject that interests the United States, Japan, Brazil, China, Russia.

03:30:01.500 --> 03:30:04.500
It's a matter of greater interest to humanity.

03:30:04.500 --> 03:30:06.500
We have to search more and advance further.

03:30:06.500 --> 03:30:16.500
Have you done any thinking about, theoretically, why this bacteria would look like bacteria

03:30:16.500 --> 03:30:23.500
occasionally found from wounds or occasionally found in animals and pets,

03:30:23.500 --> 03:30:29.500
but is very rare in humans and very rare to kill a human and to be so virulent?

03:30:29.500 --> 03:30:36.500
Do you ever think about, you know, if these beings are coming from, you know, thousands of light years away,

03:30:36.500 --> 03:30:40.500
why they would contain any sort of bacteria that might match ours?

03:30:40.500 --> 03:30:42.500
Have you gone that far in your thinking?

03:30:42.500 --> 03:30:44.500
That's an interesting question.

03:30:44.500 --> 03:30:47.500
This bacteria exists on Earth.

03:30:47.500 --> 03:30:54.500
It's extremely rare, but it exists, to our knowledge, this type of Staphylococcus.

03:30:54.500 --> 03:31:00.500
But also, the soldier, I mean, the alien or extraterrestrial,

03:31:00.500 --> 03:31:04.500
came into contact with animals at the zoo in Varginha.

03:31:04.500 --> 03:31:07.500
Some dead animals were found at the zoo.

03:31:07.500 --> 03:31:12.500
I wasn't aware of this at the time, that some dead animals were found at the zoo.

03:31:12.500 --> 03:31:19.500
Which begs the question, could it be that the extraterrestrial could have been contaminated,

03:31:19.500 --> 03:31:24.500
coming in contact with the animals and then being captured by the soldier,

03:31:24.500 --> 03:31:28.500
and therefore the soldier being contaminated by the extraterrestrial

03:31:28.500 --> 03:31:31.500
with the bacteria that was in some zoo animal?

03:31:31.500 --> 03:31:35.500
Or is the bacteria, in fact, alien, you know?

03:31:35.500 --> 03:31:39.500
That's why we're asking, and I brought this up with Dr. Hau this morning,

03:31:39.500 --> 03:31:45.500
that the CIA, NASA should support us with all the knowledge they already possess,

03:31:45.500 --> 03:31:50.500
with all their wisdom, technology and diagnostic capabilities.

03:31:50.500 --> 03:31:52.500
Brazilian medicine is very advanced,

03:31:52.500 --> 03:31:55.500
but American medicine also has its particularities.

03:31:55.500 --> 03:31:59.500
Perhaps the two of them together could conduct a more thorough scientific study

03:31:59.500 --> 03:32:03.500
of this bacteria, if the exhumation is authorized,

03:32:03.500 --> 03:32:08.500
and also of the material that must have residues where the spacecraft fell.

03:32:08.500 --> 03:32:13.500
I posed this challenge to Dr. Hau, asking you, the American people, to help us.

03:32:13.500 --> 03:32:18.500
Who told you about the ET's interaction with animals at the zoo?

03:32:18.500 --> 03:32:21.500
This is already public knowledge. This has already been reported.

03:32:21.500 --> 03:32:23.500
James Fox should know about it.

03:32:23.500 --> 03:32:28.500
I don't know which animal died. Maybe James, Fox, maybe knows.

03:32:28.500 --> 03:32:32.500
There were animals that died at the zoo during that week.

03:32:32.500 --> 03:32:36.500
So, James, I'm curious. Do you know what the nature of that interaction was?

03:32:36.500 --> 03:32:38.500
I don't think I included that part in the film,

03:32:38.500 --> 03:32:41.500
because there's so many different aspects. There were sightings later.

03:32:41.500 --> 03:32:44.500
They were like, now I'm coming to the conclusion,

03:32:44.500 --> 03:32:49.500
I think there were like a lot more beings than what were initially reported that were seen.

03:32:49.500 --> 03:32:51.500
And what did you hear about the beings?

03:32:51.500 --> 03:32:55.500
Well, we interviewed the, I guess what do you call a zoologist or the guy that, yeah.

03:32:55.500 --> 03:32:57.500
Yeah. Or a zookeeper, maybe?

03:32:57.500 --> 03:32:58.500
Yeah, he was a little more than that.

03:32:58.500 --> 03:33:00.500
So, okay, a zoologist would be like the scientist.

03:33:00.500 --> 03:33:05.500
Yeah. And he talked about that their cause of death was completely unknown.

03:33:05.500 --> 03:33:08.500
Never seen anything like it. He said it all on camera.

03:33:08.500 --> 03:33:09.500
Marco Leal could tell you more.

03:33:09.500 --> 03:33:14.500
But do we know anything about like the specific animals that the ET interacted with?

03:33:14.500 --> 03:33:19.500
Was it a cattle mutilation situation? Were they like playing in a playpen or something?

03:33:19.500 --> 03:33:23.500
They were exposed to some sort of bacteria that killed him and that he'd never really seen it.

03:33:23.500 --> 03:33:27.500
But again, I'd have to, I have an interview with a guy. I just have to reflect back on it.

03:33:27.500 --> 03:33:30.500
So those animals ended up dead.

03:33:30.500 --> 03:33:31.500
Yes.

03:33:31.500 --> 03:33:35.500
Were they typical cattle mutilations with the blood missing and incisions?

03:33:35.500 --> 03:33:38.500
No, no, no. More like just got exposed to some sort of bacteria that killed him.

03:33:38.500 --> 03:33:39.500
Got exposed to some sort of bacteria.

03:33:39.500 --> 03:33:43.500
So that would point towards the bacteria maybe not being animal.

03:33:43.500 --> 03:33:51.500
But it's so, it's just, what fascinates me so much about the bacteria is that it's something that's rare but exists on Earth.

03:33:51.500 --> 03:33:55.500
Well, here's what Dr. Janini told me, and he told me this on camera.

03:33:55.500 --> 03:33:58.500
He'd never seen anything like it before or after.

03:33:58.500 --> 03:34:02.500
Is that your experience as well?

03:34:02.500 --> 03:34:08.500
Never seen anything like this bacteria before or after, Dr. Armando?

03:34:08.500 --> 03:34:14.500
My medical practice is more focused on companies, occupational medicine, and more on private practice.

03:34:14.500 --> 03:34:24.500
My colleagues who work in the intensive care unit, the infectious disease specialists, don't see this type of infection, this kind of bacteria, on a daily basis.

03:34:24.500 --> 03:34:26.500
It exists, but it's extremely rare.

03:34:26.500 --> 03:34:30.500
And normally this infection is treated with antibiotics.

03:34:30.500 --> 03:34:44.500
And in this case, despite being a young, strong, vigorous soldier, the bacteria led to his death in just a few days, less than 10 days.

03:34:44.500 --> 03:34:47.500
